The request for evidence explains what we need from you. We will not take action on your case until we receive the evidence or the deadline to submit it expires. If you move, go to www.uscis.gov/addresschange to give us your new mailing address.

That office now has jurisdiction over your case. We sent you a notice that explains why we moved your case. Please follow the instructions in the notice. If you do not receive your notice by September 24, 2022, please go to www.uscis.gov/e-request to request a copy of the notice. If you move, go to www.uscis.gov/addresschange to give us your new mailing address.

The request for evidence explains what we need from you. We will not take action on your case until we receive the evidence or the deadline to submit it expires. If you move, go to www.uscis.gov/addresschange to give us your new mailing address.
